The paper deals with meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on learning algorithms that can quickly adapt to new tasks with limited labeled data. The paper specifically focuses on few-shot classification, which is a problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
